Mariah Carey, R&B diva and the most successful female recording artist of all time,
 follows 2005&#039;s &#039;The Emancipation Of Mimi&#039; album with her 11th studio LP &#039;E=MC2&#039;. 
In typical diva style, Carey is credited as executive producer along with Antonio 
&#039;LA&#039; Reid, the chairman of Def Jam records. Collaborators include, among others,
 Damian Marley and T-Pain on the album which, musically, ploughs the same sassy
 furrow as previous successes. Singles include the predictably catchy and sensual
 &#039;Touch My Body&#039;.
